HEADWORD: Murza
<hw>Mur"za</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>One of the hereditary
nobility among the Tatars, esp. one of the second class.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ This word must not be confounded with the Persian
<xex>Mirza</xex>, though perhaps of the same origin.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

